toItemStack(String, String) - Static method in class com.mrdimka.hammercore.common.utils.StringToItemStack
Parses string to item stack if possible, returns empty stack otherwise
Exmplee:
StringToItemStack.toItemStack(java.lang.String, java.lang.String)("minecraft:diamond_pickaxe:100@1", "{\"Example\":1}") //Returns stack with 1 diamond pickaxe and damage 100 and NBT tag that contains INT "Example" = 1
StringToItemStack.toItemStack(java.lang.String, java.lang.String)("diamond:0@16", null) //Returns stack with 16 diamonds and damage 0 and NBT is null; This example shows that items from vanilla don't have to have "minecraft:" prefix
